[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I’m Francis, ",
        "start": 6.39,
        "duration": 1.284
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 7.674,
        "duration": 2.651
    },
    {
        "text": "First, let’s prepare the bitter melon also known as goya.",
        "start": 20.787,
        "duration": 4.581
    },
    {
        "text": "Cut the goya in half lengthwise ",
        "start": 25.859,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "and run a spoon along the inside of the rind.",
        "start": 28.439,
        "duration": 3.501
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, scrape off the seeds and pith.",
        "start": 37.337,
        "duration": 3.036
    },
    {
        "text": "Make sure to remove any of the remaining pith.",
        "start": 42.803,
        "duration": 3.666
    },
    {
        "text": "Slice the goya into 3mm (0.1”) pieces.",
        "start": 48.272,
        "duration": 3.653
    },
    {
        "text": "If you are not a fan of bitter melons, ",
        "start": 52.814,
        "duration": 2.593
    },
    {
        "text": "try lettuce, spring onion leaves or bell peppers instead.",
        "start": 55.407,
        "duration": 4.719
    },
    {
        "text": "Place them into a bowl.",
        "start": 62.514,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "Sprinkle on the salt.",
        "start": 65.775,
        "duration": 1.923
    },
    {
        "text": "And toss to coat.",
        "start": 70.978,
        "duration": 1.822
    },
    {
        "text": "Let the goya sit for 5 minutes.",
        "start": 73.832,
        "duration": 3.036
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, rinse the goya in a bowl of water.",
        "start": 79.687,
        "duration": 3.535
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, remove the goya and pour fresh water over it.",
        "start": 87.953,
        "duration": 4.473
    },
    {
        "text": "Strain the goya thoroughly ",
        "start": 94.336,
        "duration": 1.987
    },
    {
        "text": "and place it onto a tray.",
        "start": 96.323,
        "duration": 2.268
    },
    {
        "text": "Thoroughly remove the excess moisture ",
        "start": 99.543,
        "duration": 2.118
    },
    {
        "text": "with a paper towel.",
        "start": 101.661,
        "duration": 1.917
    },
    {
        "text": "This process will help to reduce the bitterness of the goya.",
        "start": 103.994,
        "duration": 3.968
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, boil a generous amount of water in a pot ",
        "start": 111.07,
        "duration": 3.795
    },
    {
        "text": "and cook the somen noodles ",
        "start": 114.865,
        "duration": 1.702
    },
    {
        "text": "for slightly less cooking time than shown on the package.",
        "start": 116.567,
        "duration": 4.151
    },
    {
        "text": "The noodles should be firm ",
        "start": 120.958,
        "duration": 1.808
    },
    {
        "text": "since they will also be cooked in a pan later.",
        "start": 122.766,
        "duration": 3.691
    },
    {
        "text": "Strain the noodles with a mesh strainer.",
        "start": 131.436,
        "duration": 3.098
    },
    {
        "text": "And pour water over it to reduce the temperature.",
        "start": 136.958,
        "duration": 3.705
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, rinse the somen in a bowl of ice water.",
        "start": 143.079,
        "duration": 4.017
    },
    {
        "text": "Make sure to remove the gooey texture on the surface.",
        "start": 148.199,
        "duration": 3.75
    },
    {
        "text": "Remove the excess water thoroughly.",
        "start": 154.183,
        "duration": 2.802
    },
    {
        "text": "And place the noodles onto a plate.",
        "start": 157.235,
        "duration": 2.904
    },
    {
        "text": "Add a small amount of olive oil.",
        "start": 160.454,
        "duration": 2.986
    },
    {
        "text": "And toss to coat.",
        "start": 166.656,
        "duration": 1.768
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, let’s make the somen chanpuru.",
        "start": 170.277,
        "duration": 2.855
    },
    {
        "text": "Combine the chicken stock powder, sake ",
        "start": 173.898,
        "duration": 3.199
    },
    {
        "text": "and soy sauce.",
        "start": 178.316,
        "duration": 1.784
    },
    {
        "text": "Stir to mix.",
        "start": 181.185,
        "duration": 1.983
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, season the egg with salt ",
        "start": 185.252,
        "duration": 2.736
    },
    {
        "text": "and pepper.",
        "start": 189.087,
        "duration": 1.935
    },
    {
        "text": "Beat the egg in a bowl.",
        "start": 193.756,
        "duration": 2.035
    },
    {
        "text": "And now, heat the olive oil in a pan.",
        "start": 197.825,
        "duration": 3.268
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the chopped garlic clove, ",
        "start": 203.431,
        "duration": 2.501
    },
    {
        "text": "bitter melon ",
        "start": 206.432,
        "duration": 1.648
    },
    {
        "text": "and carrot.",
        "start": 209.621,
        "duration": 1.634
    },
    {
        "text": "Stir-fry the vegetables on medium heat.",
        "start": 214.507,
        "duration": 3.258
    },
    {
        "text": "When the carrot softens, ",
        "start": 219.878,
        "duration": 1.867
    },
    {
        "text": "add the tuna ",
        "start": 221.745,
        "duration": 1.712
    },
    {
        "text": "and moyashi bean sprouts.  ",
        "start": 225.575,
        "duration": 2.511
    },
    {
        "text": "Continue to stir-fry.",
        "start": 229.987,
        "duration": 2.251
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, gather the vegetables over to one side, ",
        "start": 233.372,
        "duration": 3.285
    },
    {
        "text": "making a space for the egg.",
        "start": 236.657,
        "duration": 2.502
    },
    {
        "text": "Pour in the beaten egg.",
        "start": 240.775,
        "duration": 2.352
    },
    {
        "text": "Cook the egg halfway through ",
        "start": 245.227,
        "duration": 2.116
    },
    {
        "text": "and combine it with the ingredients.",
        "start": 247.343,
        "duration": 2.87
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, reduce the heat to low ",
        "start": 256.017,
        "duration": 2.367
    },
    {
        "text": "and add the somen noodles.",
        "start": 258.384,
        "duration": 2.317
    },
    {
        "text": "Pour over the seasoning.",
        "start": 264.686,
        "duration": 2.172
    },
    {
        "text": "To avoid over-cooking the somen noodles, ",
        "start": 267.492,
        "duration": 2.803
    },
    {
        "text": "distribute the seasoning as quickly as possible ",
        "start": 270.295,
        "duration": 3.052
    },
    {
        "text": "and turn off the burner.",
        "start": 273.347,
        "duration": 2.234
    },
    {
        "text": "Let the ingredients absorb the seasoning.",
        "start": 277.984,
        "duration": 3.017
    },
    {
        "text": "And place the somen chanpuru onto a plate.",
        "start": 286.702,
        "duration": 3.453
    },
    {
        "text": "Sprinkle on the black pepper.",
        "start": 296.658,
        "duration": 2.436
    },
    {
        "text": "Finally, top with the bonito flakes.",
        "start": 300.377,
        "duration": 3.368
    },
    {
        "text": "Adding the moyashi bean sprouts ",
        "start": 305.865,
        "duration": 1.619
    },
    {
        "text": "will help to loosen up the somen noodles ",
        "start": 307.484,
        "duration": 2.753
    },
    {
        "text": "and also give the dish a pleasant texture.",
        "start": 310.237,
        "duration": 3.804
    },
    {
        "text": "You can also add tofu ",
        "start": 327.197,
        "duration": 1.768
    },
    {
        "text": "to make the dish more filling and nutritious.",
        "start": 328.965,
        "duration": 3.322
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen!",
        "start": 332.287,
        "duration": 1.879
    }
]